#: ../../S/September-that-never-ended.rst:5
msgid "September that never ended"
msgstr "September that never ended"

#: ../../S/September-that-never-ended.rst:7
msgid ""
"All time since September 1993. One of the seasonal rhythms of the Usenet "
"used to be the annual September influx of clueless newbies who, lacking any "
"sense of :ref:`netiquette`\\, made a general nuisance of themselves. This "
"coincided with people starting college, getting their first internet "
"accounts, and plunging in without bothering to learn what was acceptable. "
"These relatively small drafts of newbies could be assimilated within a few "
"months. But in September 1993, AOL users became able to post to Usenet, "
"nearly overwhelming the old-timers' capacity to acculturate them; to those "
"who nostalgically recall the period before, this triggered an inexorable "
"decline in the quality of discussions on newsgroups. Syn. eternal September."
" See also :ref:`AOL-`\\."
msgstr ""
"1993年9月以降のすべての時間。かつてのUsenetの季節的なリズムのひとつに、毎年9月になると、\\ :ref:`netiquette`\\ "
"の感覚を欠き、一般に迷惑をかける無知な新参者が大量に流入することがあった。これは人々が大学に入り、初めてのインターネットアカウントを手に入れ、何が許容されるかを学ぶ手間をかけずに飛び込むのと重なっていた。こうした比較的小さな新参者の流入は、数か月のうちに同化できた。しかし1993年9月、AOLのユーザーがUsenetに投稿できるようになり、古参が彼らを文化に馴染ませる能力をほぼ圧倒した。その前の時代を懐かしく思い出す者にとって、これはニュースグループの議論の質の容赦ない低下の引き金となった。eternal"
" September(永遠の9月)の同義語。\\ :ref:`AOL-`\\ も参照。"
